---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Agenda | Open for SDG Conference">
  <section style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
    <h2 style="font-size:2rem; color:#002f5f; margin-bottom:1rem;">Conference Agenda</h2>
    <p>The agenda below outlines the sequence of sessions for the Open for SDG Conference.  Times are approximate and shown in Pacific time (UTC−7).  Each thematic session begins with a short presentation followed by a panel discussion.</p>
    <div style="overflow-x:auto;">
      <table style="width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin-top:1rem;">
        <thead>
          <tr style="background:#002f5f; color:#fff;">
            <th style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem; text-align:left;">Time</th>
            <th style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem; text-align:left;">Session</th>
            <th style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem; text-align:left;">Description</th>
            <th style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem; text-align:left;">Speakers / Moderator</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <!-- Opening keynote -->
          <tr style="background:#f5f5f5;">
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">09:00–09:15</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Opening Keynote</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Welcome speech introducing the objectives of the conference</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Tiejun Huang – Prof. Peking University &amp; Chairman of BAAI</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">09:15–09:45</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Opening Keynote</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Keynote address on the power of open technologies for sustainable development</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Mehdi Snene – Chief AI Officer, OECD &amp; UN</td>
          </tr>
          <!-- Open Data session -->
          <tr style="background:#f5f5f5;">
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">09:45–10:05</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Open Data for the SDGs</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Case study: Data for Public Healthcare – exploring how open data can support public health initiatives</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Speaker TBD (Chief Data Officer at PATH)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">10:05–10:50</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Open Data Panel</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">
              Panel discussion on building an open data initiative to accelerate the SDGs. Sample topics: the role of open data, identifying gaps &amp; opportunities, mobilising collaboration and establishing guiding principles.
            </td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">
              Moderator: Yonghua Lin (BAAI)<br />
              Panelists: M.O. KHAH (UN Data Governance), Yong Qin (Nankai University) and additional guests
            </td>
          </tr>
          <!-- Open Policy session -->
          <tr style="background:#f5f5f5;">
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">10:50–11:10</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Open Policy for the SDGs</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Case study on an open‑source project aligned with the SDGs</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Speaker TBD (Asia Development Bank)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">11:10–11:55</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Open Policy Panel</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">
              Panel exploring how the UN can engage with open‑source communities and projects. Topics include governance models, contribution pathways, legal considerations and alignment with the SDGs.
            </td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">
              Moderator: Anni Lai (Generative AI Commons)<br />
              Panelists: Gael Blondelle (Eclipse Foundation), Matt White (PyTorch Foundation) and others
            </td>
          </tr>
          <!-- Open Science session -->
          <tr style="background:#f5f5f5;">
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">11:55–12:15</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Open Science for the SDGs</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Presentation on OpenSeek &amp; Open Compute and their relevance to sustainable development</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Yonghua Lin – VP &amp; Chief Engineer, BAAI</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">12:15–13:00</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Open Science Panel</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">
              Discussion on harnessing open science for the SDGs: highlighting the role of open science, identifying barriers &amp; enablers, promoting cross‑sector collaboration, addressing ethical considerations and shaping a roadmap for action.
            </td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">
              Moderator: TBD<br />
              Panelists: Sameer Chauhan (UNICC) and experts from UNU Mexico, ITU, ASEAN and other regional organisations
            </td>
          </tr>
          <!-- Future AI session -->
          <tr style="background:#f5f5f5;">
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">13:00–13:20</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Future AI for the SDGs</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Presentation: BrainU for persons with disabilities – exploring AI innovations with social impact</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Bo Lei (BAAI / BrainCo China)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">13:20–14:05</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Future AI Panel</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">
              Examining the future of AI in the context of the SDGs.  Sample discussion topics: envisioning AI for sustainable development, promoting inclusive &amp; equitable AI, bridging innovation and impact, and fostering multistakeholder collaboration.
            </td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">
              Moderator: Hilary Carter (Linux Foundation Research)<br />
              Panelists: representatives from ITU, the School of Government of South Africa, DeepSeek/Qwen/Baidu and robotics companies
            </td>
          </tr>
          <!-- Show & Tell -->
          <tr style="background:#f5f5f5;">
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">14:05–14:15</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Show &amp; Tell</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Lightning talk showcasing an open‑source project or use case for the SDGs</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Speaker TBD</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">14:15–14:25</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Show &amp; Tell</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Lightning talk showcasing an open‑source project or use case for the SDGs</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Speaker TBD</td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f5f5f5;">
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">14:25–14:35</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Show &amp; Tell</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Lightning talk showcasing an open‑source project or use case for the SDGs</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Speaker TBD</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">14:35–14:45</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Show &amp; Tell</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Lightning talk showcasing an open‑source project or use case for the SDGs</td>
            <td style="padding:0.5rem 0.75rem;">Speaker TBD</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="border-top:1px solid #eee; padding-top:1rem;">
    <h3 style="font-size:1.25rem; color:#002f5f; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Notes</h3>
    <p>All session topics and durations are proposals and may be updated.  TBD names indicate speakers to be confirmed by the organisers.  Breaks are scheduled between sessions as needed.</p>
  </section>
</Layout>